content:
The CRM Analytics Encryption solution enhances security for Salesforce customers by extending encryption capabilities to the data at rest that is stored on the Salesforce file system. 

To encrypt data at rest and preserve functionality, CRM Analytics Encryption services are built natively into the CRM Analytics platform. The solution applies strong, probabilistic encryption on data stored at rest.

As a prerequisite to CRM Analytics Encryption, you must be approved by the CRM Analytics Encryption Product Manager. Your org must have a Shield Platform Encryption tenant secret.

Data read from and written to disk is automatically encrypted with the unique key for your account when using CRM Analytics with your encryption-enabled instance.

Features include key export, Bring Your Own Key, key rotation, key revocation, and key import are available. All CRM Analytics features are supported, with the following exceptions: 

Pre-existing data is not encrypted.
Data that was in CRM Analytics before encryption was enabled is not encrypted.
If pre-existing data is imported from Salesforce objects through the dataflow, the data becomes encrypted on the next dataflow run.

Frequently Asked Questions:

Is data encrypted in transit? Yes.
Can CRM Analytics bring in data encrypted with Shield Platform Encryption? Yes.
Are the keys different for Shield Platform Encryption and CRM Analytics Encryption? Yes.
Do mobile dashboards still work with encryption? Yes.
Is there any impact on application performance? The solution is designed to have at most a minimal performance impact.
title: Salesforce CRM Analytics Encryption
